# 🎯 RayTracer – B-OOP-400 Project

This project is a modular, extensible **raytracer** developed as part of the Epitech B-OOP-400 curriculum. It simulates how rays of light interact with 3D primitives to generate photorealistic images.

---

## ✨ Features

- ✅ Ray-object intersection: spheres and planes
- ✅ Scene translation using `TranslatedPrimitive`
- ✅ Configurable camera (position, direction, FOV)
- ✅ Lighting:
  - Ambient
  - Directional
  - Point lights
- ✅ Shadow projection using shadow rays
- ✅ Scene configuration through `.cfg` files (via libconfig++)
- ✅ Output images in `.ppm` format
- ✅ Optional post-processing: `.ppm → .png`
- ✅ Several ready-to-use example scenes

---

## 🛠️ Build Instructions

### Requirements:

- C++17-compatible compiler (e.g., `g++`)
- `make`
- `libconfig++` development package
- [ImageMagick](https://imagemagick.org/) (for converting `.ppm` to `.png`)

### To build the project:

```bash
make
